    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I have an [implementation](https://github.com/mdehoog/go-ethereum/pull/15) for this change. This indeed yields a significant performance improvement when verifying multiple blob transactions:\r\n```\r\nname                 old time/op    new time/op    delta\r\nVerifyMultiple/8-6     73.9ms ± 0%    40.7ms ± 0%   ~     (p=1.000 n=1+1)\r\nVerifyMultiple/16-6     138ms ± 0%      81ms ± 0%   ~     (p=1.000 n=1+1)\r\n\r\nname                 old alloc/op   new alloc/op   delta\r\nVerifyMultiple/8-6     25.2MB ± 0%    22.1MB ± 0%   ~     (p=1.000 n=1+1)\r\nVerifyMultiple/16-6    50.4MB ± 0%    44.1MB ± 0%   ~     (p=1.000 n=1+1)\r\n\r\nname                 old allocs/op  new allocs/op  delta\r\nVerifyMultiple/8-6       400k ± 0%      301k ± 0%   ~     (p=1.000 n=1+1)\r\nVerifyMultiple/16-6      800k ± 0%      603k ± 0%   ~     (p=1.000 n=1+1)\r\n```\r\n\r\nVerifying a blob tx using merkle trees for challenges takes about 25 milliseconds on my machine (AMD Ryzen 7 3700X). With the switch to using a simple sha256 hash, it takes only 5ms to verify.",
